If UDP is blocking mode (_timeout > 0), we presume there is a race condition in the functions UDPSocket::sendto and UDPSocket::recvfrom when a multiple number threads share the socket.

When a thread enters for instance the sendto function, the mutex _lock.lock() is set. If a second thread  calls the sendto also, it will be blocked in the _lock.lock() call. Next the first caller will execute: 

```
_lock.unlock();
////// 2ND CALLER COULD BE UNBLOCKED ///////
count = _write_sem.wait(_timeout);
_lock.lock(); 
```

It can unlock the 2nd caller, but the _read_in_progress is still not cleared. As result the 2nd caller will run in a assert:
`MBED_ASSERT(!_read_in_progress);`

